        "contact": {
          "name": "API Support",
          "url": "https://www.juheapi.com"
        },
        "description": "The Air Quality Index (AQI) API provides real-time air quality data, including the AQI and specific pollutant concentrations (such as PM2.5, PM10, CO, NO2, SO2, and O3) for various locations around the world. This API helps developers integrate air quality monitoring features into applications, enabling users to make informed decisions regarding their environment and health. It covers over 1000 major cities and 9000 monitoring stations worldwide.",
        "servers": [
          {
            "description": "Production server",
            "url": "https://hub.juheapi.com"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "https://www.juheapi.com/terms-of-service",
        "title": "Air Quality Index API",
        "version": "1.0.0",
        "tagline": "Real-time Air Quality Index and pollutant readings (PM2.5, PM10, CO, NO2, SO2, O3) for cities worldwide",
        "homepage": "https://hub.juheapi.com",
        "docs_url": "https://hub.juheapi.com",
        "license_short": "Free public API provided by JuheAPI; requires an API key.",
        "license_md": "- Listed as a free public API on freepublicapis.com.\n- Access requires an `apikey` query parameter issued by JuheAPI.\n- No explicit licence terms are published with the API; consult [JuheAPI](https://hub.juheapi.com) for terms of use before redistribution.\n- CORS is reported as disabled, so browser-side calls may need a proxy.",
        "about_md": "The Air Quality Index API is hosted on [JuheAPI](https://hub.juheapi.com) and surfaces real-time air-quality readings for locations worldwide. It is catalogued on [freepublicapis.com](https://freepublicapis.com/air-quality-index-api), where it is reported to cover over 1000 major cities and 9000 monitoring stations.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n\n- The current Air Quality Index (AQI) for a queried location.\n- Concentrations for the common pollutants: PM2.5, PM10, CO, NO2, SO2, and O3.\n- Lookup by client IP address via the `/aqi/v1/ip` endpoint.\n\nAuthentication is via an `apikey` query parameter. The community catalogue reports a typical response time of around 1.3 seconds and notes that CORS is disabled, so calls are best made from a server-side component.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "aqi": "Air-quality readings — the AQI value plus pollutant concentrations (PM2.5, PM10, CO, NO2, SO2, O3) for a location, exposed under `/aqi/v1/ip` for IP-based lookup."
        },
